<div class="c230_54">
<div id="v230.54.1"><span class="H5329 s">To the chief Musician</span><span class="H5058 s"> on Neginoth</span><span class="H4905 s">, Maschil</span><span class="H1732 s">, <i>A Psalm</i> of David</span><span class="H2130 s">, when the Ziphims</span><span class="H935 s"> came</span><span class="H559 s"> and said</span><span class="H7586 s"> to Saul</span><span class="H1732 s">, Doth not David</span><span class="H5641 s"> hide</span><span class="H3467 s"> himself with us? Save</span><span class="H430 s"> me, O God</span><span class="H8034 s">, by thy name</span><span class="H1777 s">, and judge</span><span class="H1369 s"> me by thy strength</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.54.2"><span class="H8085 s">Hear</span><span class="H8605 s"> my prayer</span><span class="H430 s">, O God</span><span class="H238 s">; give ear</span><span class="H561 s"> to the words</span><span class="H6310 s"> of my mouth</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.54.3"><span class="H2114 s">For strangers</span><span class="H6965 s"> are risen up</span><span class="H6184 s"> against me, and oppressors</span><span class="H1245 s"> seek</span><span class="H5315 s"> after my soul</span><span class="H7760 s">: they have not set</span><span class="H430 s"> God</span><span class="H5542 s"> before them. Selah</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.54.4"><span class="H430 s">Behold, God</span><span class="H5826 s"> <i>is</i> mine helper</span><span class="H136 s">: the Lord</span><span class="H5564 s"> <i>is</i> with them that uphold</span><span class="H5315 s"> my soul</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.54.5"><span class="H7725 s">He shall reward</span><span class="H7725 s"> †</span><span class="H7451 s"> evil</span><span class="H8324 s"> unto mine enemies</span><span class="H6789 s">: cut them off</span><span class="H571 s"> in thy truth</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (mine…: Heb. those that observe me)</span></div>
<div id="v230.54.6"><span class="H5071 s">I will freely</span><span class="H2076 s"> sacrifice</span><span class="H3034 s"> unto thee: I will praise</span><span class="H8034 s"> thy name</span><span class="H3068 s">, O LORD</span><span class="H2896 s">; for <i>it is</i> good</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.54.7"><span class="H5337 s">For he hath delivered</span><span class="H6869 s"> me out of all trouble</span><span class="H5869 s">: and mine eye</span><span class="H7200 s"> hath seen</span><span class="H341 s"> <i>his desire</i> upon mine enemies</span>.</div></div>
